'F FORMAT' IS A BASIC SUBROUTINETHAT   DISPLAYS A FLOATING POINTNUMBER        ACCORDING TO ASPECIFIED FORMAT.BEFORE CALLING THE SUBROUTINE; SETX TO THE NUMBER TO DISPLAY AND F TOTHE VALUE w.n; WHERE n IS THE NUMBEROF PLACES TO THE RIGHT OF THEDECIMAL ANDw IS THE TOTAL WIDTH OF THE NUMBER;INCLUDING BLANKS; DIGITS; DECIMALPOINT;AND; IF NEGATIVE; SIGN.  wSHOULD FALL  WITHIN THE RANGE OF n+3TO n+10.